WEBVTT

00:13.448 --> 00:15.493
<i>Surgeons are</i>
<i>put through rigorous tests</i>

00:15.537 --> 00:18.061
<i>just to get in the game.</i>

00:18.105 --> 00:21.456
<i>We endure decades of</i>
<i>anxiety-provoking acronyms --</i>

00:21.499 --> 00:24.285
<i>SAT, MCAT,</i>

00:24.328 --> 00:26.765
<i>USMLE, ABSITE.</i>

00:27.766 --> 00:29.029
<i> And if we pass that gauntlet...</i>

00:30.813 --> 00:34.469
<i>...we are rewarded with the</i>
<i>need to log 850 surgeries</i>

00:34.512 --> 00:38.255
<i>and take an 8-hour</i>
<i>multiple-choice and oral exam.</i>

00:38.299 --> 00:40.910
<i>There's almost no time</i>
<i>to take in the victory...</i>

00:40.953 --> 00:42.085
<i>or even a nap.</i>

00:42.129 --> 00:44.740
Oh.
I didn't really peg you

00:44.783 --> 00:46.089
for the private jet
and limo type.

00:46.133 --> 00:48.091
Don't worry.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.571
I will never send you
a private jet <i>or</i> a limousine.

00:49.614 --> 00:51.051
Okay.
Catherine Fox sent both,

00:51.094 --> 00:52.443
but thank you
for doing this here.

00:52.487 --> 00:53.618
Well, you found me
the perfect recipient,

00:53.662 --> 00:55.098
so I should be thanking you.

00:55.142 --> 00:57.231
And I've never been in a stretch
limo, so it's a win/win.

00:57.274 --> 00:58.449
Is that it?

00:58.493 --> 00:59.885
- Hey, Dr. Miranda Bailey.
- Mm-hmm.

00:59.929 --> 01:02.714
Meet Dr. Nick Marsh.
Hi.

01:02.758 --> 01:04.325
I'm not a hugger,
- but I'm gonna hug you.
- Oh!

01:04.368 --> 01:05.630
- May I hug you?
- Yeah, of course.

01:05.674 --> 01:06.718
Oh. Thank you.

01:06.762 --> 01:07.806
We need this.
Yes.

01:07.850 --> 01:08.894
Grey-Sloan needs this.

01:08.938 --> 01:10.374
Thank you!

01:10.418 --> 01:12.115
They're ready to do
the ICU conversion.
Mm.

01:12.159 --> 01:13.769
Oh, and are the residents
prepped and ready?

01:13.812 --> 01:15.292
They are ready
but not prepped.

01:15.336 --> 01:18.034
Good. I like an element
of surprise.

01:19.557 --> 01:20.689
Why are we standing
out here?

01:20.732 --> 01:21.733
That's a live organ.

01:21.777 --> 01:22.734
- Let's move!
- Right.

01:27.174 --> 01:29.741
Ow!

01:29.785 --> 01:32.266
Mom, what --
what are you doing here?

01:32.309 --> 01:33.267
What is this?

01:33.310 --> 01:34.746
Your mail.

01:34.790 --> 01:36.400
It's been piling up.

01:36.444 --> 01:38.968
You need to come in
for the residency review today.

01:39.011 --> 01:41.927
Yeah, I got the e-mail.
I'm busy.

01:41.971 --> 01:44.147
So you're just good
that our program

01:44.191 --> 01:45.757
is being slaughtered
on social media?

01:45.801 --> 01:47.150
What are you talking
about?

01:47.194 --> 01:50.327
its residents dry.

01:53.069 --> 01:55.463
and will murder you.

01:55.506 --> 01:56.812
Ow.

01:56.855 --> 01:58.814
But you may not
have seen them,

01:58.857 --> 02:01.208
but I'm pretty sure the Medical
Accreditation Council did.

02:01.251 --> 02:03.123
Oh, my God.

02:03.166 --> 02:05.473
Levi...

02:05.516 --> 02:09.912
I know you've been hurting,
but I've worked too hard.

02:09.955 --> 02:11.740
I have worked too hard
to let them come in

02:11.783 --> 02:13.655
and just shut down
our program.

02:13.698 --> 02:16.005
So please, if you have
any fight in you,

02:16.048 --> 02:18.181
any at all, get up.

02:18.225 --> 02:20.444
And come to work
just for one day!

02:21.793 --> 02:25.710
If not for yourself,
then for me, please.

02:32.239 --> 02:33.196
No.

02:33.240 --> 02:34.980
Mom!

02:35.024 --> 02:37.374
Now, I can't tell you
what to say

02:37.418 --> 02:39.246
to the accreditation council,

02:39.289 --> 02:43.293
but they will be assessing
the attendings

02:43.337 --> 02:44.381
as well
as the residents,

02:44.425 --> 02:46.427
so if they do question you,

02:46.470 --> 02:48.472
keep your answers
short and sweet,

02:48.516 --> 02:50.822
focused on the success
of the program.

02:50.866 --> 02:52.868
Do we know what questions
they're going to ask?

02:52.911 --> 02:54.739
It's a complaint-driven
site visit,

02:54.783 --> 02:56.872
so they'll want to check
our case logs,

02:56.915 --> 02:59.614
observe our residents,
review our curriculum...

02:59.657 --> 03:03.661
...and verify we are <i>all</i> staying
on top of our certifications.

03:03.705 --> 03:04.793
Do we know who complained?

03:04.836 --> 03:06.577
No, and we're not allowed
to ask.

03:06.621 --> 03:08.362
Well, how are
we supposed to show
our teaching skills

03:08.405 --> 03:09.885
with the residents
on grand rounds today

03:09.928 --> 03:11.800
with Grey and Marsh?

03:11.843 --> 03:14.759
Grand rounds today
is a miracle.

03:14.803 --> 03:16.674
Groundbreaking medicine,

03:16.718 --> 03:18.546
visiting surgeons,

03:18.589 --> 03:20.765
extraordinary
teaching opportunities --

03:20.809 --> 03:23.203
see, that's what makes
Grey-Sloan Grey-Sloan.

03:23.246 --> 03:25.770
And what happens if
they're not as impressed
with us as you are?

03:25.814 --> 03:27.207
Well, the program
goes onto probation

03:27.250 --> 03:28.599
and potentially
could be shut down.

03:28.643 --> 03:31.211
And that record would be
visible to the public.

03:31.254 --> 03:33.343
So we could lose our residents
<i>and</i> our patients.

03:33.387 --> 03:35.606
Yes.
No.

03:35.650 --> 03:39.262
Because we are going to
show them who we really are --

03:39.306 --> 03:42.613
one of the top five teaching
hospitals in the country

03:42.657 --> 03:44.528
with a world-renowned
surgical program.

03:44.572 --> 03:48.750
So, go fill in your departments
and your fellow attendings.

03:48.793 --> 03:50.491
Now go impress somebody!

03:56.453 --> 03:58.890
Ay-ay-ay-ay.

03:58.934 --> 04:02.677
Oh, no. You are scheduled
to be first interviewed.

04:02.720 --> 04:05.375
Uh, well,
it's not gonna work.

04:05.419 --> 04:06.898
And why not?

04:06.942 --> 04:08.596
My physician assessment
is in half an hour.

04:08.639 --> 04:10.424
You're doing that <i>today?</i>

04:10.467 --> 04:12.774
Inconvenient timing but I'm not
in control of the schedule.

04:12.817 --> 04:14.079
W--

04:16.038 --> 04:17.257
I think you're
all gonna see something

04:17.300 --> 04:19.084
you haven't seen before.

04:19.128 --> 04:20.651
Hi.
Hi.

04:20.695 --> 04:22.653
So, this is Mason Taylor.

04:22.697 --> 04:25.613
He was declared brain dead after
being struck by a drunk driver.

04:25.656 --> 04:27.092
We're just
procuring organs?

04:27.136 --> 04:28.355
How is this a grand rounds?

04:28.398 --> 04:29.269
Do you two have questions?

04:30.618 --> 04:31.923
Um...Um...

04:31.967 --> 04:34.448
Uh, oh, yeah, uh,
if he's the donor,

04:34.491 --> 04:35.884
then what's
in the cooler?

04:35.927 --> 04:37.494
Oh, I'm sorry.
Did I not mention

04:37.538 --> 04:40.367
that Mr. Taylor
will also be the recipient?

04:40.410 --> 04:42.064
We're giving him a kidney.

04:42.107 --> 04:44.284
We're donating a kidney
to a brain-dead recipient?

04:44.327 --> 04:47.156
Did the kidney donor family
consent to this?

04:48.636 --> 04:50.768
The kidney donor is a pig --

04:50.812 --> 04:53.771
farm-raised,
genetically modified.

04:53.815 --> 04:56.078
We're doing
a xenotransplant.

04:56.121 --> 04:58.820
You're putting a pig kidney
into a human man?

04:58.863 --> 05:00.430
- That's right.
- A brain-dead human man?

05:00.474 --> 05:01.649
That's right.

05:01.692 --> 05:04.304
- I --
- Perez?

05:04.347 --> 05:06.218
I'm just <i>so</i> confused.

05:09.918 --> 05:13.095
Um, how do I explain to the team
reviewing our residency

05:13.138 --> 05:14.662
that you are unavailable?

05:14.705 --> 05:16.098
Just tell them the truth.

05:16.141 --> 05:18.492
Look, I am the director
of the residency program.

05:18.535 --> 05:20.755
I requested this assessment
myself.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.365
That speaks highly
of the standards

05:22.409 --> 05:24.149
to which
we hold ourselves,

05:24.193 --> 05:26.195
and the residency council
will appreciate that.

05:26.238 --> 05:27.631
Will they?

05:27.675 --> 05:29.024
I hope so.

05:29.067 --> 05:31.940
You can hope, or you can
postpone the assessment!

05:31.983 --> 05:33.681
Look, I see your worry --
okay? --

05:33.724 --> 05:35.160
and I understand it.

05:35.204 --> 05:37.249
But we have flown
a world-class surgeon

05:37.293 --> 05:40.644
and a neuroscientist here
according to their scheduling.

05:40.688 --> 05:43.081
I went out of my way to find
someone who doesn't like me

05:43.125 --> 05:45.170
and won't be biased,
which wasn't easy to do

05:45.214 --> 05:46.868
because
I'm pretty popular.

05:46.911 --> 05:49.261
Okay, let's just take
a deep breath, Bailey, okay?

05:49.305 --> 05:51.263
You are
my residency director.Ah.

05:51.307 --> 05:54.441
Our program is being assessed
as to whether or not

05:54.484 --> 05:56.443
it should be allowed
to continue.

05:56.486 --> 05:57.618
Now,
what if you don't pass?

05:57.661 --> 05:59.533
Richard Webber.

05:59.576 --> 06:02.405
Uh, uh, David, yeah.
Thank you for coming.

06:02.449 --> 06:03.928
Wait,
he's your evaluator?

06:03.972 --> 06:06.975
I wanted someone
as unbiased as they come.

06:07.018 --> 06:09.107
Plus, I'm an expert
at judging people.

06:09.151 --> 06:10.761
I can spot a tremor
from a mile away.

06:10.805 --> 06:11.893
He doesn't have
any tremors.

06:11.936 --> 06:13.024
Well, we're also
looking for

06:13.068 --> 06:14.591
any intellectual tremors,
if you will.

06:14.635 --> 06:16.680
Less obvious than the physical
but equally significant.

06:16.724 --> 06:18.029
He doesn't have
any of those either.

06:18.073 --> 06:20.380
Dr. Bartley is as good
a neuroscientist

06:20.423 --> 06:22.643
as you will find in these
contiguous United States.

06:22.686 --> 06:25.385
And together, we will be
the judge of that.

06:25.428 --> 06:27.256
Chief Bailey.

06:27.299 --> 06:29.345
Jamarah Blake,
Medical Accreditation Council.

06:29.389 --> 06:31.042
- Yes.
- Yikes.

06:31.086 --> 06:32.217
Busy day.

06:32.261 --> 06:33.305
Shall we?

06:33.349 --> 06:35.786
Shall we?
Yeah.

06:37.222 --> 06:40.356
Mnh.

06:52.629 --> 06:55.719
Hey! Richard.
I just wanted to wish you luck.

06:55.763 --> 06:58.026
And how'd you know? I said nothing.

06:58.069 --> 06:59.723
I grew up with an extremely
withholding mother.

06:59.767 --> 07:01.943
I can squeeze information
out of "good morning."

07:01.986 --> 07:03.510
Thank you, but I don't --
I don't need any luck.

07:04.685 --> 07:06.687
Just a time machine.

07:09.037 --> 07:10.168
Cool.

07:10.212 --> 07:12.432
Way to poke holes
in his trust in me.

07:12.475 --> 07:13.911
Well, he doesn't have to
trust <i>you,</i>

07:13.955 --> 07:15.217
he has to trust <i>himself.</i>

07:15.260 --> 07:16.610
And I have been helping him
do that

07:16.653 --> 07:18.481
in his weakest moments
for years.

07:18.525 --> 07:21.049
- Mm-hmm.
- He has to pass this test.

07:21.092 --> 07:23.355
I-I am not saying
don't be truthful.

07:23.399 --> 07:28.012
I'm just saying he's important
to this hospital and to me.

07:30.275 --> 07:32.408
How long have you...

07:32.452 --> 07:36.760
I'll show you the skills labs,
simulators, residents' lounge,

07:36.804 --> 07:38.283
as well as our lecture hall

07:38.327 --> 07:40.503
where we hold our didactics
and grand rounds.

07:40.547 --> 07:41.678
But when
do you have us scheduled

07:41.722 --> 07:43.811
to speak with
the residents directly?

07:43.854 --> 07:45.682
I was hoping to start with
Dr. Schmitt.

07:45.726 --> 07:48.816
They are, uh,
actually observing

07:48.859 --> 07:51.035
a groundbreaking
medical innovation today.

07:52.689 --> 07:54.604
Okay, everyone say,
"Thank you, Mason."

07:56.258 --> 07:58.956
Mason here wanted to
donate his organs,

07:59.000 --> 08:01.742
but UNOS ruled it out due to
his history of cancer.

08:01.785 --> 08:03.700
So instead, his wife consented
to donating

08:03.744 --> 08:05.833
his whole body to research.

08:05.876 --> 08:08.052
Listen, 17 people die
each and every day

08:08.096 --> 08:09.532
waiting for
a kidney transplant.

08:09.576 --> 08:11.578
If this works,
we could say goodbye

08:11.621 --> 08:15.059
to long transplant lists
in just a few years.

08:15.103 --> 08:16.408
So...

08:16.452 --> 08:18.498
- Thank you, Mason.
- Good.

08:18.541 --> 08:20.195
Alright.
Now, what does this one do?

08:20.238 --> 08:21.979
Oh, whoa, okay.
Wha-- Oh, I got it. Okay.

08:28.812 --> 08:30.379
Is this the first time
anyone's done this?

08:30.422 --> 08:32.599
Yep. Who can tell me why
we're working on a dead man?

08:32.642 --> 08:33.774
First, do no harm.

08:33.817 --> 08:35.427
Exactly.
We can't experiment

08:35.471 --> 08:38.213
with a xenotransplant on anyone
who has anything to lose.

08:38.256 --> 08:40.215
And why are we attaching
the kidney to the groin?

08:40.258 --> 08:41.346
So that you can see
the kidney

08:41.390 --> 08:42.913
while you're assessing
its performance.

08:42.957 --> 08:45.568
We'll actually see the kidney
darken if rejection happens.

08:45.612 --> 08:47.962
Also, the groin is
close to the bladder,

08:48.005 --> 08:50.573
which provides a good blood
supply through the iliac artery.

08:50.617 --> 08:52.270
- Wow. Correct.
- Mm.

08:52.314 --> 08:54.708
I don't care what
Dr. Grey says about you --

08:54.751 --> 08:56.579
you guys are
a pretty sharp group.

08:58.146 --> 09:00.191
You have one minute to make
that side look like that side.

09:00.235 --> 09:01.410
Well, I'm not a toddler.

09:01.453 --> 09:02.629
Again, we'll be the judge
of that.

09:02.672 --> 09:04.805
And go.

09:09.418 --> 09:10.680
It's impressive that

09:10.724 --> 09:12.247
you're still bringing in
innovative cases

09:12.290 --> 09:14.641
when you've lost --
let me see -- um...

09:14.684 --> 09:16.381
seven physicians
recently?

09:16.425 --> 09:17.861
Well, we've had a lot
of retirees this year.

09:17.905 --> 09:19.167
- Ah.
- Mm-hmm.

09:19.210 --> 09:21.604
So did Dr. Hayes,
chief of peds, retire?

09:21.648 --> 09:23.214
Actually, he moved
back to Ireland.

09:23.258 --> 09:25.347
I was told
it was a family matter.

09:25.390 --> 09:26.522
Yeah.
Huh.

09:26.566 --> 09:27.784
We have urine.
He peed!

09:28.829 --> 09:30.570
We got urine!

09:30.613 --> 09:32.354
Oh, my God!

09:32.397 --> 09:34.138
Okay, I'm gonna
give them this.

09:34.182 --> 09:35.270
Dr. Bailey,
we have urine.

09:35.313 --> 09:36.793
Yeah! So we heard!

09:36.837 --> 09:38.273
Uh, D-Dr. Grey,

09:38.316 --> 09:40.797
this is the team from
the accreditation council.

09:40.841 --> 09:43.583
It's nice to meet you.
Uh, it's a big deal.

09:43.626 --> 09:45.933
So, obviously the residents
are very excited.

09:45.976 --> 09:48.588
Th-The residents
are always enthusiastic

09:48.631 --> 09:49.850
when they work with
Dr. Grey.

09:49.893 --> 09:51.503
Well, I would imagine so.

09:51.547 --> 09:54.376
And it seems like a rare
opportunity these days.

09:54.419 --> 09:56.160
You're a busy woman,
Dr. Grey.

09:56.204 --> 09:57.814
I am.

09:57.858 --> 09:59.816
I actually have
a liver biopsy to get to.

09:59.860 --> 10:01.644
It's a pleasure to meet
both of you.

10:01.688 --> 10:03.428
- I'll see you soon.
- Nice to meet you.

10:04.604 --> 10:06.388
- Mm. So, Dr. Bailey?
- Yeah.

10:06.431 --> 10:07.824
Who's next?

10:07.868 --> 10:09.826
Yes.

10:12.220 --> 10:13.743
What about this one?

10:13.787 --> 10:17.660
